@startuml "Abb-ZETA-Client-Statement-mit-Android-Attestation"
!include ../puml-layout.txt

!pragma teoz true

box "Device" DEVICE_COLOR
  participant "TEE / StrongBox\n(Hardware Security)" as TEE LEI_COMPONENT_COLOR
  participant OS as "OS (Android)" LEI_COMPONENT_COLOR
  box "Primärsystem" PRIMAERSYSTEM_COLOR
    participant Client as "ZETA Client" <<zeta>>
  end box
end box

box "Anbieter TI 2.0 Dienst" PROVIDER_COLOR
  box "ZETA Guard" ZETA_GUARD_COLOR
    participant AuthS as "PDP\nAuthorization Server" <<zeta>>
  end box
end box


Client++
OS++
TEE++
Client -> AuthS ++ : GET /nonce
AuthS --> Client -- : Nonce

alt Android Key / ID Attestation
  Client -> OS: Ermittle Posture\n(OS-Version, Security Patch Level,\nHersteller, Modell, Verified Boot,\nApp-Signaturinformationen)
  OS --> Client: Posture-Daten (Klartext)
Client -> Client: clientDataHash =\nSHA-256(Nonce || Posture-Daten || PuK.Client.Sig)

  Client -> OS: Signature.sign(\n  KeyStore.getKey(Alias_AK),\n  clientDataHash)
  OS -> TEE: Signiere clientDataHash\nmit PrK.AK.Sig
  TEE --> OS: ECDSA Signatur
  OS --> Client: signed_client_data_hash

  note left of Client
    android_key_attestation_certificate_chain wurde beim DCR übermittelt; kein erneutes
    Erzeugen eines Schlüsselpaars. AuthS verifiziert: attestationChallenge im
    Blatt-Zertifikat == SHA-256(PuK.Client.Sig).
  end note

  opt Play Integrity API (ergänzend)
    Client -> OS: IntegrityTokenProvider.request(\nrequestHash = clientDataHash)
    OS --> Client: integrityToken\n(JWS: deviceIntegrity + appIntegrity + accountDetails)
  end
  Client -> Client: Generiere client-statement\n(Evidence = signed_client_data_hash,\nandroid_key_attestation_certificate_chain,\n[integrityToken], Posture-Daten im Klartext)
else Software Attestation (Fallback)
  Client -> Client: Generiere client-statement\n(OS und PS Daten ungesichert)
end

@enduml